Antennomeres 17, the basal 6 glabrous, the antenna reaching back to tergite 2. Head capsule without sutures. Ocelli very small. Coxosternal teeth 4+4. Basal sutures of tooth plates forming an obtuse angle, with short, weak longitudinal suture (
Fig. 1
). Forcipular femoroid process not clearly visible (no inner teeth).

Tergite 1 just overlapping hind border of head capsule. Tergites 2–20 with complete paramedian sutures, those on 2–7 diverging anteriorly (
Fig. 2
). With short anterior lateral sutures on 2–17 (the 
kurzen vorderen Schrägfurchen
of tergites 3–15 described by 

for 

T. afer

). Only tergite 21 marginate, without median suture, the hind border angular, its apex rounded (
Fig. 3
).

Sternites 2–20 with complete paramedian sutures. Sternite 21 with sides somewhat convergent, the hind border straight (rhomboidal) (
Fig. 4
). Coxopleuron with 2 end spines, 1 subapical spine and 1 side spine (3 spines on the end and 2 on dorsal ridge is incorrect).
